Commentary: offcutter, and it proves quite profitable for Afghanistan. The line is ever so straight, pesky for a batsman looking to free the arms. Porterfield moves outside leg to try and drive it over extra cover, but Rashid Khan there, times his jump perfectly to take the catch over his head

Dismissal_text: WTS Porterfield c Rashid Khan b Karim Janat 22 (26m 15b 1x4 2x6) SR: 146.66

Commentary: gets down on one knee and launches it to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to O'Brien, 1 run

Commentary: good shot, but he can't pick the gap between point and short third man. Picked the quicker, shorter delivery outside off. Would be disappointed his late cut didn't result in more
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Wilson, 1 run

Commentary: googly does him. Two wickets in eight balls since the resumption. This one is the result of the legspinning slowing it down, tossing it up, and tempting O'Brien into a big hit. Aims for a slog sweep over midwicket. Misses it altogether and is bowled
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to O'Brien, OUT
Dismissal_text: KJ O'Brien  b Rashid Khan 5 (8m 8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 62.50

Commentary: quicker, flatter and fuller outside off, drives to the left of point
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to McBrine, 1 run

Commentary: Is that another wicket? Afghanistan believe they have got Wilson stumped and the third umpire will have to adjudicate on it. Googly again from Rashid, nicely tossed up, to draw the batsman under pressure to hit boundaries forward. Wilson goes for a cover drive, clearly he didn't pick the variation. The ball hurtles through bat and pad, Shahzad tips the bails over ever so quickly and Wilson's foot is on the line. That means he's outta here
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Wilson, OUT
Dismissal_text: GC Wilson st †Mohammad Shahzad b Rashid Khan 1 (4m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: looks for the reverse sweep - showing every sign of his nerves, he premeditates the stroke, and the fuller, faster delivery outside off is past him before he knows it
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Tucker, no run

Commentary: another Irishman  goes out swinging. It's a length ball on middle, McBrine wants to smack it out of the ground. There is no time to get yourself in. Not even the time to steady this awful wobble. He has to go, and the slog to cow corner only goes as far as the fielder in the deep
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to McBrine, OUT
Dismissal_text: AR McBrine c Mohammad Nabi b Karim Janat 1 (5m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: they've been trying so very very hard and finally Tucker picks up a slower ball and slogs it between deep midwicket and long-on. It's all high-risk cricket
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Tucker, FOUR runs

Commentary: races down the pitch, gets a thick outside edge to a short delivery outside off and with third man up, Sadiq pays the price for bowling his normal pace. This is a field set for the slower ball
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Tucker, FOUR runs

Commentary: cramps the batsman up with a fuller delivery on middle and leg. Tucker swings from the hip, only makes contact off the thigh pad
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Tucker, 1 leg bye

Commentary: plants a shortish delivery on leg stump into the captain's hands at extra cover
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to GJ Thompson, 1 run

Commentary: slices a full delivery, swinging into him rather late, to long-off, who comes running in off the boundary
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Tucker, 1 run

Commentary: third wicket in seven balls for the leggie. He's changed the game. Of course, having a target that forces the batsman to look for the big hits help. Here Tucker comes dancing down and pops a catch to the man at long-off
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Tucker, OUT
Dismissal_text: L Tucker c Najibullah Zadran b Rashid Khan 9 (9m 6b 2x4 0x6) SR: 150.00

Commentary: looks for the reverse sweep again, but the length ball is a little too wide for him to make proper connection
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to GJ Thompson, no run

Commentary: goes for the conventional sweep this time and still fails to connect
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to GJ Thompson, no run

Commentary: now the frustrated batsman loses his head, comes down the track and is done in by the googly. Superb bowling from Rashid. He ladled all the pressure on Thompson and then gave him a way out - the tossed up ball, but it spins in, skittles through bat and pad as he slogs, and Shahzad does the rest
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to GJ Thompson, OUT
Dismissal_text: GJ Thompson st †Mohammad Shahzad b Rashid Khan 1 (7m 4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 25.00

Commentary: appeal for lbw and it's given. Rashid has five wickets in 10 balls - on he is a hat-trick as well. Although this one seems to be a bit lucky. The debutant McCarthy goes for a sweep and is struck on the back pad. Appears to be outside the line of off stump
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to McCarthy, OUT
Dismissal_text: BJ McCarthy lbw b Rashid Khan 0 (1m 1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: wanders outside off stump for a sweep, Rashid bowling a loopy legbreak, exactly where the batsman is, still beats him. That's a triple-wicket maiden
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Mulder, 1 bye

Commentary: down the track, but he ends up yorking himself. Nudge to long-on for a couple. There's a direct hit at the non-strikers'. A quick check on if the run has been complete. And it is.
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Mulder, 2 runs

Commentary: tosses it up outside off, because the batsman is making room outside leg, and Nabi essentially one-ups him. The ball is too wide for Mulder to make any connection
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Mulder, no run

Commentary: comes down and flicks a straight delivery to short fine leg
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Mulder, 1 run

Commentary: bludgeons a half-volley down the ground, and its got enough power to beat the man at long-off, to his right
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Dockrell, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball outside off, slugs it to long-on
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Dockrell, 1 run

Commentary: steps down, Nabi throws it wide of his reach, slogs it to the right of long-on, who sends in another direct hit. Mulder's safe, but Ireland are not.
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Mulder, 2 runs
